% Shepard bibliography — canonical BibTeX source.
%
% This file is the SSOT for citations used across the shepard docs site,
% aidocs/, and design discussions. Every aidocs/* document that cites a
% paper / standard / software adds an entry HERE in the same PR.
%
% Rendered by Jekyll via `docs/_data/references.yml` (auto-generated by
% `scripts/bib2yml.py`, which is wired into `.github/workflows/pages.yml`).
%
% Citation keys are stable. They are referenced by:
%   - inline links from docs/*.md (rendered through site.data.references.<key>)
%   - aidocs/*.md notes (prose mentions; reviewers grep the .bib)
%
% Categories (used to group entries on the bibliography page):
%   standards    — W3C, ISO, DIN, OGC, CCSDS, IEC
%   regulations  — EU acts, national/EU regulations, EASA rules
%   papers       — peer-reviewed publications and pre-prints
%   software     — software citations (cff / GitHub repos)
%   ontologies   — vocabularies (OWL/SKOS/SHACL graphs)
%   policy       — policy reports, white papers, position statements
%   dlr_internal — DLR publications, eLib entries, DLR press releases

% ============================================================
